 <text>
  <front>
   <head>To the Right Honourable the Earl of Thomond, at Bath; who charg'd the Author with making an Irish Bull.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">, we're in Story told,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Thy Ancestors wore Crowns of old:</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">In fair  Isle they reign'd;</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">A Country, by their Sons disdain'd!</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Too apt to charge their Native Isle</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">With ev'ry Vice of Speech and Style:</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Yet thy , great and good,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Of , and of  Blood,</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">(Whose Ancestors, to Fame well known,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">When injur'd, shook the  Throne;)</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Will not thy native Isle deride,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Tho' to an higher Crown ally'd.</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And shall  fear Disgrace,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">From , of  Race?</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">It ill becomes thee thus to treat</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Thy Family's Imperial Seat.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">look down and see</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">This Change in thy Posterity;</l>
     <l n="19" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Who quit all Titles to thy Throne,</l>
     <l n="20" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But Hospitality alone.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
